[[Category:Latin root equ]]

==Latin==
[[Category:la:Mammals]]

===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: ['ekwus]

===Alternative spellings===
* [[equos]] ''(till the middle of the first century B.C.)''
* [[ecus]] ''(the regular development, later remodeled to ''equus'' on the analogy of the stem ''equ-'' as remained, e.g., in the genitive'' equi.)

===Etymology===
From [[Proto-Indo-European]] '''*ekwos''', ''horse''. Originally palatal, the k became a gutteral in the centum languages, of which Latin is one. In the segmentation, *ekw-o-, the American Heritage Dictionary relates *ekw- to the adjective, '''*oku-''', ''swift.'' A horse is thus ''the swift one'', which fits the circumstance of Indo-European mobility.

===Noun===
'''equus''', '''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin second declension|equi]]''' ''m''

